  "text": "The ext_authz (External Authorization) filter in Envoy (v1.31.2) implements authorization decision control through three main mechanisms: per-route bypass configuration, authorization decision processing with immediate response paths, and route cache clearing logic.\n\n## Per-Route Bypass Configuration\nThe per-route bypass functionality is implemented in:\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h` (lines 231-273): The `FilterConfigPerRoute` class defines the per-route configuration structure with a `disabled_` field that specifies whether the filter should be bypassed for a specific route.\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc` (lines 810-827): The `getPerRouteFlags()` method retrieves the per-route configuration and determines if the check should be skipped based on whether the route has the filter disabled.\n\nThe bypass logic in the filter's request processing:\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc` (lines 226-232): In `decodeHeaders()`, the `skip_check_` flag is set from the per-route configuration. If this flag is true, the filter returns `Continue` immediately, bypassing the authorization check.\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc` (lines 280, 300): The skip check flag is also checked in `decodeData()` and `decodeTrailers()` to prevent buffering and authorization calls for bypassed routes.\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/config.h` (line 108-110): The global `denyAtDisable()` method and the per-route override control whether to deny requests when the filter is disabled.\n\n## Authorization Decision and Immediate Response Path\nThe immediate response path is handled in:\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc` (lines 403-769): The `onComplete()` callback processes the authorization service response and implements three distinct paths:\n  - **OK path (lines 432-676)**: Applies header/query parameter mutations from the authorization response, clears route cache if needed, and calls `continueDecoding()` to allow the request to proceed.\n  - **Denied path (lines 678-737)**: Calls `sendLocalReply()` to return an immediate response to the client without further filter processing, sending the status code and headers from the authorization service.\n  - **Error path (lines 739-768)**: Handles authorization service errors with configurable failure mode behavior (allow or deny).\n\nRoute cache clearing is implemented:\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.cc` (lines 436-441): When `clearRouteCache()` is enabled in the global configuration and the authorization response modifies request headers or query parameters, the filter clears the route cache to allow the request to be re-evaluated against routing rules based on the modified attributes.\n\n## Failure Mode and Control Logic\nThe filter includes several control mechanisms:\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/ext_authz.h` (lines 57-159): The `FilterConfig` class defines global configuration including `failure_mode_allow()`, `denyAtDisable()`, `clearRouteCache()`, and `filterEnabled()` methods that control filter behavior.\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/config.h` (lines 14-33): Configuration factory that creates the filter with gRPC or HTTP authorization service clients.\n\n## Authorization Service Communication\nThe actual communication with authorization services is abstracted through:\n- `source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz.h` (lines 146-168): The `Client` interface defines the abstract contract for authorization service communication.\n- `source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz_grpc_impl.h` and `.cc`: Implements gRPC client for communicating with gRPC authorization services, processing `CheckResponse` messages.\n- `source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/ext_authz_http_impl.h` and `.cc`: Implements HTTP client for communicating with HTTP authorization services, converting HTTP responses into authorization decisions.\n- `source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/check_request_utils.h` and `.cc`: Builds `CheckRequest` messages by extracting attributes from HTTP request headers, stream info, and metadata.\n\n## Request Flow\nWhen a request arrives:\n1. `decodeHeaders()` checks if the route has the filter disabled via `getPerRouteFlags()`. If disabled, returns immediately.\n2. If enabled, `initiateCall()` builds a `CheckRequest` using `CheckRequestUtils` and sends it to the authorization service via the `Client` interface.\n3. The authorization service responds, and `onComplete()` processes the response:\n   - If OK: applies mutations and continues, optionally clearing route cache.\n   - If Denied: returns immediate local response via `sendLocalReply()`.\n   - If Error: handles with failure mode logic (allow or deny based on configuration).\n4. Request continues through remaining filters or reaches upstream server based on authorization decision.\n\nThe proto file `api/envoy/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/v3/ext_authz.proto` defines the configuration schema including `ExtAuthzPerRoute` with the `disabled` field and `CheckSettings` for per-route customization."
